---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="Research access — Bulk and programmatic access to Robertium"
  description="Programmatic and bulk access to the Robertium hypothesis catalog and knowledge graph for biomedical researchers."
  current="api"
  ogImage="/og/api.png"
>
  <section class="hyp-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <h1>Research access</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">Bulk and programmatic access to the Robertium hypothesis catalog and knowledge graph</p>
      <p class="meta" style="font-family: inherit; font-size: 16px; color: var(--text-secondary); line-height: 1.7; max-width: 760px;">
        For most researchers, the public web catalog at <a href="/hypotheses" style="color:var(--accent);">/hypotheses</a> is enough. If you need bulk download, programmatic queries, or a copy of the underlying graph for an offline analysis, email and we'll work it out. There is no signup or paywall — this page describes what is currently available and what is planned.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container--narrow">
      <div class="section-header">
        <div class="section-icon"><svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg></div>
        <h2>Available now</h2>
      </div>
      <ul class="simple-list">
        <li><strong>Hypothesis catalog as JSON</strong> — the same file the website renders is publicly served at <a href="/data/hypotheses.json" style="color:var(--accent);"><code style="font-family:var(--font-mono); font-size:14px;">/data/hypotheses.json</code></a>. No authentication. Includes outreach-quality hypotheses with full evidence chains (PMIDs, titles, scores, mediator/drug/outcome metadata). Updated when the cross-domain orchestrator is re-run.</li>
        <li><strong>Knowledge graph dump (Kuzu format)</strong> — available on request. The complete graph with all 81,328 entities and 140,178 claim edges across six therapeutic domains. Useful if you want to run your own ABC queries, swap in different filters, or merge with other graphs.</li>
        <li><strong>Raw claims database</strong> — available on request. Postgres dump of the structured claims table (subject, predicate, object, polarity, confidence, source PMID) for all 47,255 papers that passed the L1 biomedical-relevance filter. Useful if you want to apply your own extraction quality thresholds or re-derive hypotheses.</li>
        <li><strong>Open-source pipeline</strong> — the full ingest, extraction, and orchestration code is at <a href="https://github.com/routewise96/robertium" style="color:var(--accent);">github.com/routewise96/robertium</a> under MIT. Clone the repo, drop in an OpenAlex concept ID for a new domain, and run the pipeline on your own corpus. Cost on cloud LLM APIs is roughly $3–$7 per 5,000 papers.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section--gray">
    <div class="container--narrow">
      <div class="section-header">
        <div class="section-icon"><svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/><polyline points="12 6 12 12 16 14"/></svg></div>
        <h2>Planned</h2>
      </div>
      <p>A REST API for direct programmatic queries against the live catalog and graph. The intent is to expose endpoints along these lines:</p>
      <ul class="simple-list">
        <li><code style="font-family:var(--font-mono); font-size:14px;">GET /hypotheses?drug=X&amp;mediator=Y&amp;outcome=Z</code> — filter the catalog by any combination of fields</li>
        <li><code style="font-family:var(--font-mono); font-size:14px;">GET /hypotheses/{'{id}'}</code> — single hypothesis with full evidence chain</li>
        <li><code style="font-family:var(--font-mono); font-size:14px;">GET /entities/{'{name}'}</code> — all claims and cross-domain occurrences for a named entity</li>
        <li><code style="font-family:var(--font-mono); font-size:14px;">GET /evidence/{'{pmid}'}</code> — every claim extracted from a given paper</li>
      </ul>
      <p>What ships first depends on what people actually need. If you have a use case — even a rough one — email it. That signal is more useful than a roadmap.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container--narrow">
      <div class="section-header">
        <div class="section-icon"><svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M4 4h16c1.1 0 2 .9 2 2v12c0 1.1-.9 2-2 2H4c-1.1 0-2-.9-2-2V6c0-1.1.9-2 2-2z"/><polyline points="22,6 12,13 2,6"/></svg></div>
        <h2>Request access</h2>
      </div>
      <p>For the graph dump, the raw claims database, or to discuss a programmatic use case:</p>
      <div class="data-cta">
        <a href="mailto:daniel@robertium.com?subject=Research%20access" class="btn btn--primary">
          <svg width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M4 4h16c1.1 0 2 .9 2 2v12c0 1.1-.9 2-2 2H4c-1.1 0-2-.9-2-2V6c0-1.1.9-2 2-2z"/><polyline points="22,6 12,13 2,6"/></svg>
          Email daniel@robertium.com
        </a>
        <a href="https://github.com/routewise96/robertium" class="btn btn--secondary">
          <svg width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="currentColor"><path d="M12 0C5.37 0 0 5.37 0 12c0 5.31 3.435 9.795 8.205 11.385.6.105.825-.255.825-.57 0-.285-.015-1.23-.015-2.235-3.015.555-3.795-.735-4.035-1.41-.135-.345-.72-1.41-1.23-1.695-.42-.225-1.02-.78-.015-.795.945-.015 1.62.87 1.845 1.23 1.08 1.815 2.805 1.305 3.495.99.105-.78.42-1.305.765-1.605-2.67-.3-5.46-1.335-5.46-5.925 0-1.305.465-2.385 1.23-3.225-.12-.3-.54-1.53.12-3.18 0 0 1.005-.315 3.3 1.23.96-.27 1.98-.405 3-.405s2.04.135 3 .405c2.295-1.56 3.3-1.23 3.3-1.23.66 1.65.24 2.88.12 3.18.765.84 1.23 1.905 1.23 3.225 0 4.605-2.805 5.625-5.475 5.925.435.375.81 1.095.81 2.22 0 1.605-.015 2.895-.015 3.3 0 .315.225.69.825.57A12.02 12.02 0 0024 12c0-6.63-5.37-12-12-12z"/></svg>
          Clone the pipeline
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
